00:11:31.116 --> 00:11:32.486 A:middle
You can see that I got that.

233
00:11:33.096 --> 00:11:34.006 A:middle
Anything else?

234
00:11:34.156 --> 00:11:36.536 A:middle
Well, how did we get it?

235
00:11:37.716 --> 00:11:40.816 A:middle
Similar to the way we encoded
it, we just simply decode it.

236
00:11:41.046 --> 00:11:42.886 A:middle
And when you write this
code and you look at it,

237
00:11:43.116 --> 00:11:45.106 A:middle
the code itself is very simple.

238
00:11:46.326 --> 00:11:48.256 A:middle
What's interesting
is when you think

239
00:11:48.256 --> 00:11:51.136 A:middle
about how your application is
structured and see what it is

240
00:11:51.136 --> 00:11:52.696 A:middle
that you need to
save and restore.

241
00:11:52.806 --> 00:11:54.546 A:middle
The code is very boilerplate.

