00:11:56.516 --> 00:11:59.816 A:middle
We also kept track of whether or
not we were showing those bars.

243
00:12:00.466 --> 00:12:03.976 A:middle
Again, we just simply
decoded Boolean and set it up.

244
00:12:04.436 --> 00:12:06.646 A:middle
Now, I'm not showing you
the code that actually goes

245
00:12:06.646 --> 00:12:08.766 A:middle
and draws the image
and sets the title.

246
00:12:09.766 --> 00:12:10.846 A:middle
In your application,

247
00:12:10.896 --> 00:12:13.046 A:middle
you've already written
the code that does that.

248
00:12:13.306 --> 00:12:15.716 A:middle
When you first presented
that image view controller

249
00:12:15.716 --> 00:12:19.686 A:middle
or used the segway transition,
you obviously have some code

250
00:12:19.856 --> 00:12:21.406 A:middle
that goes and loads
in the image.

251
00:12:21.666 --> 00:12:23.036 A:middle
And with state restoration,

252
00:12:23.486 --> 00:12:25.276 A:middle
you'll always be
able to reuse that.

253
00:12:25.276 --> 00:12:28.376 A:middle
So here, all we're trying to do
is get the information we need

254
00:12:28.376 --> 00:12:29.556 A:middle
and then pass it around.

255
00:12:29.746 --> 00:12:32.546 A:middle
And I'll show you that in
a little more detail later.

256
00:12:32.546 --> 00:12:36.926 A:middle
So do we have to
do anything else?

257
00:12:36.926 --> 00:12:37.686 A:middle
I mean, we had a lot

