464
00:22:51.716 --> 00:22:55.286 A:middle
However, that array contains
the identifiers for all

465
00:22:55.286 --> 00:22:56.966 A:middle
of the restoration parents.

466
00:22:57.126 --> 00:22:59.906 A:middle
That way if you've scoped it
and you want to be informed

467
00:22:59.906 --> 00:23:02.606 A:middle
about which one of these
objects we're asking for,

468
00:23:02.956 --> 00:23:04.276 A:middle
you have that information.

469
00:23:06.576 --> 00:23:09.556 A:middle
We also pass in the
coder that was used

470
00:23:09.866 --> 00:23:11.536 A:middle
when you initially
saved the object.

471
00:23:11.856 --> 00:23:13.566 A:middle
So why do we do that?

472
00:23:13.566 --> 00:23:15.196 A:middle
Why not just let you
create an object.

473
00:23:15.866 --> 00:23:17.076 A:middle
Well, you're probably
going to go

474
00:23:17.076 --> 00:23:18.696 A:middle
through some initialization
code,

475
00:23:18.936 --> 00:23:22.306 A:middle
you may need some resources, and
