1263
01:00:36.156 --> 01:00:38.126 A:middle
so that I could kill
the application

1264
01:00:38.386 --> 01:00:40.156 A:middle
without losing state
restoration.

1265
01:00:40.546 --> 01:00:42.716 A:middle
And it's really useful
when you're chasing a bug

1266
01:00:42.716 --> 01:00:45.426 A:middle
or you just want to check things
and you want to be able to go

1267
01:00:45.426 --> 01:00:51.226 A:middle
on the switcher and kill it but
not actually lose the archive.

1268
01:00:51.786 --> 01:00:53.646 A:middle
So we did a recap.

1269
01:00:53.646 --> 01:00:55.976 A:middle
I'm hoping that if you
haven't used state restoration,

1270
01:00:56.256 --> 01:00:59.056 A:middle
this shows you just how easy
it can be to incorporate it

1271
01:00:59.116 --> 01:01:02.536 A:middle
in your app, and you'll go back
and you'll want to take a look

1272
01:01:02.536 --> 01:01:03.906 A:middle
at this and see what you can do.

1273
01:01:04.486 --> 01:01:06.296 A:middle
And for those of you who
have already been using it

1274
01:01:06.296 --> 01:01:09.976 A:middle
and new people as well, I hope
that the new features show you

1275
01:01:09.976 --> 01:01:11.816 A:middle
that you can also extend things

1276
01:01:11.816 --> 01:01:13.826 A:middle
and it makes it even
easier to use.

